@thenameslibbyy Salads but like good salads are your best friend. Add plenty of nuts/seeds for protein and texture. Also frick iceberg lettuce. Kale, spinach, and romaine lettuce are all much better options.

@thenameslibbyy Overnight oats/chia puddings make for great breakfasts, same with avocado toast and fried eggs. If you're also gluten free like me, try gluten free bread. The one I have is made with like rice and flax flour I think and it's actually really good.

@thenameslibbyy Currently dealing with something similar. No bake protein balls (literally like a cup of oats, a cup of peanut butter, a scoop of protein powder, and 1/3 of a cup of honey or maple syrup. Combine with rubber spatula then roll into balls with your hands and freeze for 20 min)
